when  we  were  putting  together  our  own  plans  for  economic  devel-
opmental  opportunities,  I  think—yes,  just  continuing  to  share  the 
information, because there’s—the plans that we have put into place 
and  the  opportunity  that  we  had  for  leverage  from  becoming  part 
of  this  Olympic  family  are  ones  that  you  can  take  along  and  start 
right now. 

Carl  and  I  were  talking  earlier  before  this  began  about  how  im-
portant  it  is  for  people  like  yourself  involved  in  the  industry  to  go 
to those games, if you get a chance. 

We’re  going  to  be  going  to  the  Torino  Games,  and  we’re  not  just 
going  to  learn  the  lessons  of  how  to  put  them  on,  but  I’m  respon-
